# Jan Awaaz 🗳️ — People's Voice

800 million Indians voted in 2024.
Most civic tools were built for none of them.

This one is different.

---

## Why I built this 💙

Every election, millions of people walk into a polling booth completely lost.

They don't know if their candidate ever kept a promise.
They don't know they can reject every candidate using NOTA.
They don't know what to do if someone turns them away at the booth.

Not because they don't care about their country.
Just because nobody ever built something for them.

Jan Awaaz means People's Voice.
And that's exactly what this is.

---

## Who is this for? 🙋

### 🌱 First time voters
Never voted before? Scared of getting it wrong? This app holds your hand through every single step in simple language you actually understand. And if reading is hard, just press the speaker button and the app talks to you.

### 🧠 Informed citizens
Want to know if your local candidate actually did what they promised last time? The Candidate Report Card shows you every promise they made — and whether they kept it, broke it, or are still working on it.

### 🏛️ Researchers and officials
Need legal citations, ECI guidelines, RTI templates, or a complaint letter generator? The Expert mode has you covered with clean structured data and real tools.

---

## What it does ✨

🌍 Works in 12 Indian languages
Hindi, English, Tamil, Telugu, Bengali, Marathi, Kannada, Malayalam, Punjabi, Gujarati, Odia, Urdu. Switch language and the whole app changes — including the color theme based on your region!

🔊 Talks to you
Every section has a voice reader. Because not everyone can read and that should never stop someone from knowing their rights.

📊 Candidate Report Card
See criminal cases, assets declared, education, and past promises all in one place. No digging through 10 different websites.

✅ Am I ready to vote?
Answer 4 simple questions and the app tells you exactly where you stand and what to do next.

💥 Myth Crusher
Think voting takes the whole day? Think your one vote doesn't matter? This section will surprise you. Rate your confidence before the answer drops and see how many things you were confidently wrong about 😅

⚖️ Your rights at the booth
Most voters don't know half their rights. This section lays them all out simply. And if your rights are violated, Expert mode generates a proper complaint letter for you in seconds.

🤝 Voter Pledge
Make a promise to vote and share it with your friends on WhatsApp. Small thing, big impact.

---

## The honest part 🙏

Right now Jan Awaaz runs on demo data to show you what it can do.

The dream version connects live to the Election Commission of India's data, MyNeta.info for real candidate records, and Google News for live election updates.

This is just the beginning.

